===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|might}}, {{m|enm|myghte}}, (also {{m|enm|maught}}, {{m|enm|macht}}, {{m|enm|maht}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|miht}}, {{m|ang|mieht}}, {{m|ang|meaht}}, {{m|ang|mæht||might, bodily strength, power, authority, ability, virtue, mighty work, miracle, angel}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*mahtiz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*mahtuz||might, power}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*mógʰtis}}, {{m|ine-pro|*magʰ-||to allow, be able, help}}, corresponding to Germanic {{m|gem-pro|*maganą}} + {{m|gem-pro|*-þiz}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|micht}}, {{m|sco|maucht||might}}, {{cog|frr|macht||might, ability}}, {{cog|fy|macht||might, ability}}, {{cog|nl|macht||might, power}}, {{cog|de|Macht||power, might}}, {{cog|sv|makt||might}}, {{cog|is|máttur||might}}. Related to {{m|en|may}}.

